<Author>osm80
<Content>Pleasantly surprised I was worried about going to this hotel because of some of the reviews I had read. But I was pleasantly surprised. The hotel was an easy 10 minute walk from a main Metro stop, and it was very easy to find. I arrived at 9pm and walked from the Metro to the hotel, and it was very straightforward. Although a walk to Port Olympia is a bit of a trek, but doable in comfy shoes!The hotel itself is very nice, trying hard to be plush but not too tacky. The staff were extremely friendly and very helpful and made my party and myself feel very welcome. There was some noise on the first night from the other guests arriving in from a night out, but the second night was very peaceful, just the usual city sounds could be faintly heard.The pool is more for relaxing in than for swimming, but it was all clean and nicely presented. The gymnasium has all the basic equipment you would need to keep on top of your exercise routine.I didn't eat at the restaurant on a evening, but the breakfasts were superb.Overall, this hotel was excellent value for money and I would definitely stay there again if I go to Barcelona, although I would not fly into Barcelona Girona airport as this is over an hour's bus journey away, and was somewhat of a shock to find out! 
